(296, 1, '2020-07-22 10:27:30', '2020-07-22 10:27:30', '<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n<div class=\"blog_men_block bg-white\">\r\n<div class=\"news_detail mt-3\">\r\n\r\nNepal Disaster Volunteer Coordination Network organised it\'s another meeting on 19 July 2015 at Solteemod, Kathmandu. In the meeting, Taplejung Team debriefed about the Relief Distribution and Psychosocial First Aid Programme – Taplejung, which they have completed recently in July 2015. According to them, they have distributed relief materials to altogether 290 flood and landslide survivors, four schools, one sub-health post, and one health assistant of six VDCs of Taplejung district. They also provided psychosocial first aid to the survivors of all the affected VDCs. The meeting was then followed by rechecking action plan and preparing an action plan for the network.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-4\">\r\n<div class=\"news_right_block \">\r\n<div class=\"news_right_title\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'ANOTHER MEETING OF NEPAL DISASTER VOLUNTEER COORDINATION NETWORK', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'another-meeting-of-nepal-disaster-volunteer-coordination-network', '', '', '2023-09-11 10:39:46', '2023-09-11 10:39:46', '', 0, 'https://cwin.org.np/new/?post_type=news&#038;p=296', 0, 'news', '', 0),
