(301, 1, '2020-12-02 10:29:45', '2020-12-02 10:29:45', 'Child Workers in Nepal Concerned Centre (CWIN) celebrated its 28th anniversary on 20 November in Kathmandu with a slogan \'Creation of New Nepal with Children\'.\r\n\r\nIn the programme organised to mark the celebration, CWIN inaugurated a musical album – \'Hami Balika\' that includes voices of girls from CWIN Balika Peace Home. Some musical performances from the album were also presented live by the girls in the programme.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, CWIN also felicitated 40 students who just passed the School Leaving Certificate exam in this year. It also felicitated its staffs who have spent ten years involving in CWIN\'s campaigns. A documentary based on CWIN\'s relief programme after the devastating earthquake-2015 was also shown during the programme.', '28TH ANNIVERSARY OF CWIN', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28th-anniversary-of-cwin', '', '', '2023-09-11 10:39:57', '2023-09-11 10:39:57', '', 0, 'https://cwin.org.np/new/?post_type=news&#038;p=301', 0, 'news', '', 0),
