(309, 1, '2021-06-13 10:33:46', '2021-06-13 10:33:46', 'On June 12, 2016, to mark World Day against Child Labour, ECPAT in Nepal (CWIN Nepal, Maiti-Nepal, Shakti Samuha and ECPAT Luxembourg) organized a release of<a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20220113065925/http://globalstudysectt.org/global-report/offenders-on-the-move/?pid=113&amp;aid=432&amp;sa=1\"> “Global Study of Sexual Exploitation of Children in Travel and Tourism”</a> in Kathmandu, Nepal.\r\n\r\nECPAT in Nepal would like to extend deepest gratitude to the Chief Guest Honorable Minister of Culture, Tourism and Civil Aviation Mr Aananda Prasad Pokharel , Executive Director of CCWB, Mr Tarak Dhital and Executive Director of Nepal Telecommunication Authority Mr. Ananda Raj Khanal for showing solidarity against Sexual Exploitation of Children in Travel and Tourism (SECTT).\r\n\r\nThe organizers would also like to thank the members from different Government, non-government, international nonprofit organizations and print and television media for attending the “Global Study of Sexual Exploitation of Children in Travel and Tourism” and showing their solidarity against SECTT. We would also like to thank ECPAT International Secretariat for their guidance and support.', 'Report Released on \'Global Study of Sexual Exploitation of Children in Travel and Tourism\'', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'report-released-on-global-study-of-sexual-exploitation-of-children-in-travel-and-tourism', '', '', '2023-09-11 10:40:24', '2023-09-11 10:40:24', '', 0, 'https://cwin.org.np/new/?post_type=news&#038;p=309', 0, 'news', '', 0),
