(332, 1, '2022-10-20 10:54:43', '2022-10-20 10:54:43', 'Capacity-building Training for Civil Society Organizations (CSOs) on Children\'s Rights to a Healthy Environment was carried out in Kathmandu on 16th October. Members of different civil society organizations working in the sector of Children\'s Rights participated in the training. Environmental Expert Bhusan Tuladhar shed light on the roles of humans in the degradation of the environment. The main trainer of the day Mr. Tuladhar also discussed the ways of mitigation and adaptation against the effects of Climate Change in the program. The participants further discussed the role of CSOs in protecting Childrens\' Rights to a Healthy Environment. The program was organized by CWIN Nepal with the support of Child Rights Coalition Asia (CRC Asia).', 'Capacity-building Training for CSOs on Children\'s Rights to a Healthy Environment completed', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'capacity-building-training-for-csos-on-childrens-rights-to-a-healthy-environment-completed', '', '', '2023-09-11 10:55:25', '2023-09-11 10:55:25', '', 0, 'https://cwin.org.np/new/?post_type=news&#038;p=332', 0, 'news', '', 0),
