(356, 1, '2023-08-02 11:05:50', '2023-08-02 11:05:50', 'CWIN Nepal completed a mental health orientation for the members of the National Adolescent Girls\' Network and National Adolescent Boy Network. 26 representatives from all 7 provinces participated in the online orientation. The psychiatrists and the experts from Kanti Children\'s Hospital Children and Adolescent Mental Health Department informed the participants about the mental health issues faced by adolescents in Nepal. The participants were also made aware of the support mechanisms available to cope with mental health issues.\r\n\r\nWednesday, 19th July 2023\r\n\r\nThe participants discussed the Chatbot \"Ma Chhu Ni\" and its accessibility through various communication apps like Facebook, WhatsApp, and Viber. The Chatbot was designed to facilitate communications between the experts from the mental health department at Kanti Hospital and the children and adolescents in need of medical support. CWIN Nepal launched the Chatbot with the support of Kanti Children\'s Hospital and UNICEF. Since last year, CWIN-Nepal has also started telemedicine services to help solve mental health problems in hospitals and health centers in different parts of the country. CWIN Nepal along with Kanti Children\'s Hospital and Nepal Telecom has issued a toll-free number 166001 10666 with the target of reaching more children and adolescents who are in need of support and counselling regarding mental health issues.', 'Online Orientation for Adolescent Girls and Boys on Mental Health', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'online-orientation-for-adolescent-girls-and-boys-on-mental-health', '', '', '2023-09-11 11:06:19', '2023-09-11 11:06:19', '', 0, 'https://cwin.org.np/new/?post_type=news&#038;p=356', 0, 'news', '', 0),
